    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required credibility level. One factor (Test conditions, required level 3, achieved level 2) is below the required level due to testing at a single load rate per ASTM F1717. This gap is accepted given the standardized nature of the protocol, the medium model risk level, and the medium decision consequence. All three QoIs satisfy pre-specified quantitative acceptance criteria (relative error < 10%, E/uval < 1.96). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible for the stated COU.",
